Witness ReporterANC chief whip Dr Makhosi Khoza, who last week resigned from the KZN Legislature, has been appointed chief executive officer at Akani Retirement Fund Administrators.Akani describes itself as being the administrator of the largest pension fund in the local government sector, the Municipal Employees&rsquo; Pension Fund. Khoza&rsquo;s resignation was announced last week by ANC provincial secretary Sihle Zikalala, who said she was joining the private sector. He had no further details and Khoza could not be contacted. Akani announced&rsquo;s Khoza&rsquo;s appointment in an advert in the Sunday Times money and careers section. The advert said Akani Financial Services Group had diversified its portfolio and owned Destiny Exclusive Hotels, Munghana Travel and Tourism as well as Akani Property Development. It welcomed Khoza&rsquo;s appointment, noting her extensive local government experience.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.